17 of multiple parcels shall only have one vote, not one vote per parcel. Multiple owners of
18 one parcel shall have one vote which shall be cast by one of their number designated in
19 writing by such multiple owners as their elector."
20 SECTION 2.
21 Said Act is further amended by revising Section 5 as follows:
22 "SECTION 5.
23 Administration, appointment, and election of board members
24 (a)(1) Pursuant to Article IX, Section VII, Paragraph III of the Constitution of the State
25 of Georgia, each district created pursuant to this Act shall be administered by a board
26 composed of five board members to be appointed and elected as hereinafter provided.
27 One board member shall be appointed by the majority vote of a quorum of the city
28 council of the City of Rincon, Georgia. One board member shall be appointed by the city
29 manager of the City of Rincon, Georgia. The remaining three board members shall be
30 elected by a caucus of electors representing the owners of real property within the district
31 subject to taxes, fees, and assessments levied by the board. Elected board members shall
32 each serve for a term of four years, respectively. The appointed board members shall
33 serve at the pleasure of the governing body and city manager who appointed them,
34 respectively. The city council of the City of Rincon may, after adoption of a resolution,
35 provide for a district created pursuant to this Act to be administered by a board composed
36 of seven board members, with the sixth and seventh board members shall be elected as
37 provided for in this Act.
38 (2) Each elected board member shall be an elector, as defined in paragraph (7) of
39 Section 3 of this Act. In the event that an elected board member ceases to be an elector
