40 as required by this subsection, such board member's position shall be declared vacant as
41 of the date such person ceases to qualify as an elector.
42 (b) A board shall elect one of its number as chairperson, another as vice chairperson, and
43 shall also elect a secretary and a treasurer or a secretary-treasurer, either of whom may, but
44 need not, be a member of the board. Board members shall receive no compensation for
45 their services but shall be reimbursed for actual expenses incurred in the performance of
46 their duties.
47 (c) Board members shall be subject to recall in an election called by either:
48 (1) A resolution of the city council of the City of Rincon; or
49 (2) A petition signed by one-third of the electors of the district.
50 (d) The initial board members to be elected as provided in this Act shall be elected in a
51 caucus of electors, which shall be held within 60 days after the adoption of a resolution of
52 the city council of the City of Rincon setting the time and place within the district after
53 notice thereof shall have been given to such electors by publishing notice thereof in the
54 legal organ of Effingham County once a week for four weeks prior to such caucus.
55 Thereafter, there shall be conducted annually, not later than 60 days following the last day
56 for filing ad valorem property tax returns in Effingham County, a caucus of such electors
57 at such time and place within the district as the board shall designate in such notice for the
58 purpose of electing board members to those positions which have terms expiring or are
59 vacant. If a vacancy occurs in an elected position on the board, the board shall, within 60
60 days thereafter, call a special election to fill such vacancy to be held within 60 days of the
61 call unless the vacancy occurs within 180 days of the next regularly scheduled election, in
62 which case a special election may, but need not, be called. For any election held under the
63 provisions of this Act, notice of such election shall be given to the electors by publishing
64 notice thereof in the legal organ of Effingham County once a week for four weeks prior to
65 such caucus.
